
#########################################################
###     Role : apply_ilo_firmware Usage (HP ONLY)     ###
#########################################################
Purpose:
    Update the ILO firmware on a provided ILO IP address

Structure:
    tasks:
        - main.yml
    library:
        - apply_ilo_firmware.py

main.yml:
    Calls on the custom ansible role "library/apply_ilo_firmware.py"

    Requirements: (
        ip_address host var [xx.xx.xx.xx]
        ilo_username group var [username]
        ilo_password group var [password]
    )

    +-------------- Call Custom Role --------------+
    |   apply_ilo_firmware:                        |
    |       ip_address:     "{{ ip_address }}"     |
    |       ilo_username:   "{{ ilo_username }}"   |
    |       ilo_password:   "{{ ilo_password }}"   |
    +----------------------------------------------+

apply_ilo_firmware.py:
    Takes the passed "{{ ip_address }}", "{{ ilo_username }}", "{{ ilo_password }}" and tries to connect via the hpilo python module.
    It then polls the ILO for the current ILO firmware version.
    If it is less than the set latest version, then it will upgrade following the set steps.
    ILO will be upgraded to each step until latest level reached.

    Requirements: Manually set in module(
        MAX_FW_VERSION : string - Example->"2.55"
        FIRMWARE_STEPS : list() - Example->['1.05','1.40','2.00']
        FW_LOCATIONS: dict() - Example->{'1.05': '/path/to/bin/file','1.40': '/path/to/bin/file'}
    )

